documentation_summary: AutoGluon.core version 1.0.0, released on November 30, 2023, is a Python package for automated machine learning (AutoML) focusing on image, text, time series, and tabular data. It simplifies the process of applying machine learning, allowing users to easily train and deploy high-accuracy models with minimal code. The package requires Python versions 3.8 to 3.11 and is licensed under the Apache Software License (Apache-2.0). It is developed and maintained by the AutoGluon Community, with contributions welcomed. The project's documentation provides comprehensive guides and examples for installation, usage, and maximizing model accuracy.
